Hannaford

post_text:
Parents & Guardians,



As part of the WOCSD school closure distance learning plan, school nutrition services will provide bagged breakfasts and lunches at no charge to all students interested. To gauge interest we ask parents & guardians to email a lunch request one day in advance to Cpasternak@WOCSD.org. If you do not have access to email please call the school nutrition office (207)-646-7872 and leave a message with your daily order. The lunches will be available for daily pickup at Wells Elementary School from 8:30 AM to 10:30 AM in the main entrance. If you have any questions contact Chris Pasternak Director of Nutrition Services.

Sincerely,

Chris Pasternak

Director of Nutrition Services

207-646-7872

post_text:
Wells High School preparing to cull the Class of 2018’s student records

Wells High School will be culling student records for the Class of 2018 beginning in early October. If you would like to obtain your cumulative folder, please send your request, including your name and mailing address, in writing to guidance secretary Erin Sanborn by September 30, 2019. You can either email your request to her at esanborn@wocsd.org or mail your request addressed to Erin Sanborn, Wells High School Guidance Office, 200 Sanford Road, Wells, ME 04090. The culling process will continue as time permits throughout the 2019-20 school year.

post_text:
Wells High School held its 116th Commencement at Warrior Memorial Field on June 9th. At that time 100 percent of this year’s senior class ─one hundred and ten students-received their diplomas in the graduation ceremony. Kimberly Towne was the Class of 2019 Valedictorian and Natalie Robinson was Class Salutatorian. This year’s commencement speaker was Bob Crowley a retired Gorham High School physics teacher from Durham, Maine who, in
2008, competed and won in the 17th season of CBS’s reality show, “Survivor”.

The graduation was video recorded for later airing on Spectrum cable channel 1301 in Wells and channel 1302 in Ogunquit. The cablecast in these towns will begin June 27th and will run the following days and times through July 12th : Wednesdays and Thursdays at 4 pm, and Fridays,
Saturdays and Sundays at 8 pm.

If you do not have access to Spectrum you can also view graduation via YouTube at https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EV-y1iLRzCI

post_text:
Congratulations to Manny Diggs
On February 9, the Universal Technical Institute held their Top Tech Challenge 36 teams from all across New England competed and 6 of those teams were from Maine. Manny Diggs and his teammate took first place and the other team from PATHS took second. A team from Lewiston Regional Technical Center took third. Sanford took ninth. Four of the six teams from Maine placed in the top 10. For winning, Manny Digss and his teammate both received a $10,000.00 scholarship to UTI and won the school $4,000.00 in tools and a toolbox.
text:
Congratulations to Manny Diggs
On February 9, the Universal Technical Institute held their Top Tech Challenge 36 teams from all across New England competed and 6 of those teams were from Maine. Manny Diggs and his teammate took first place and the other team from PATHS took second. A team from Lewiston Regional Technical Center took third. Sanford took ninth. Four of the six teams from Maine placed in the top 10. For winning, Manny Digss and his teammate both received a $10,000.00 scholarship to UTI and won the school $4,000.00 in tools and a toolbox.

We have recently learned that Meetinghouse Road in Wells is currently closed due to debris and trees down from high winds.
This will impact school bus service to that area - in particular, Bus #12.
Buses will arrive as soon as the road is opened and conditions permit.
We appreciate your patience and understanding.

post_text:
Wells High School to Cull Student Records

The Wells High School Guidance Department will be culling student files for the Class of 2017 beginning October 1, 2018. If you would like to obtain your file, please
send your request in writing along with your name and mailing address to guidance secretary, Erin Sanborn, by September 30, 2018. You may either email her at esanborn@wocsd.org or mail your request addressed to Erin Sanborn, Wells High School, Guidance Office, 200 Sanford Rd, Wells, ME 04090.
